1
00:03:23,510 --> 00:03:26,361
We're riding towards Absolution.

2
00:03:26,361 --> 00:03:29,188
You know how far west we are?

3
00:03:36,984 --> 00:03:38,981
Maybe he's a dummy.

4
00:03:39,587 --> 00:03:42,903
Is there a reason you're not
answering my question?

5
00:03:42,991 --> 00:03:46,358
Look here Pa.
He's got iron on his wrist.

6
00:03:46,358 --> 00:03:48,290
He's been shot.

7
00:03:48,290 --> 00:03:52,560
Could be he done broke out of hoosegow.
Might be worth bounty-money.

8
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:55,255
That could be.

9
00:04:01,782 --> 00:04:04,517
It's not your lucky day, stranger.

10
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:08,480
Turn around and start walking.

11
00:04:09,573 --> 00:04:12,271
I said turn around
and start walking.

12
00:07:02,536 --> 00:07:04,418
Get out.

13
00:07:40,916 --> 00:07:43,068
Hello?

14
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:38,317
Balls to heaven, friend.

15
00:08:38,542 --> 00:08:40,591
Easy now.

16
00:08:46,731 --> 00:08:50,592
Alright, turn around,
nice and slow.

17
00:08:51,211 --> 00:08:53,461
I've been shot.

18
00:08:59,536 --> 00:09:01,786
Only two kinds of men get shot.

19
00:09:01,786 --> 00:09:04,618
Criminals and victims.

20
00:09:05,036 --> 00:09:07,460
Well, which one are ya?

21
00:09:07,906 --> 00:09:09,550
I don't know.

22
00:09:09,804 --> 00:09:12,503
You got a name, friend?

23
00:09:12,505 --> 00:09:14,000
I don't know that either.

24
00:09:15,090 --> 00:09:17,573
Well, just what do you know?

25
00:09:18,078 --> 00:09:20,156
English.

26
00:09:26,912 --> 00:09:31,369
Well, that... That's a right
odd-looking wound there.

27
00:09:32,541 --> 00:09:35,200
Looks almost cauterised.

28
00:09:35,790 --> 00:09:38,052
Now this might sting a bit.

29
00:09:40,103 --> 00:09:43,140
There you go.
- Is this a mining town?

30
00:09:45,626 --> 00:09:48,831
Yeah. Well, that was the notion.

31
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:52,259
People moved on though...

32
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:54,218
...for gold.

33
00:09:54,318 --> 00:09:57,206
Alright now, try and hold still.

34
00:09:59,827 --> 00:10:01,792
There we go.

35
00:10:02,953 --> 00:10:05,452
This is no gunshot.

36
00:10:05,705 --> 00:10:08,430
Where did ya get this, son?
- I don't know.

37
00:10:08,686 --> 00:10:13,184
Well I can't rightly absolve you of your sins,
If you don't recall now, can I?

38
00:10:13,184 --> 00:10:16,961
That being said, I've seen
good men do bad things

39
00:10:16,961 --> 00:10:19,615
bad men do good things.

40
00:10:20,278 --> 00:10:22,865
Whether you're gonna end up
in heaven or hell...

41
00:10:23,194 --> 00:10:25,956
it's not God's plan,
that's your own.

42
00:10:26,596 --> 00:10:29,188
You just gotta remember
What it was.

43
00:10:29,188 --> 00:10:32,426
Alright, put your finger
right here. Come On.

44
00:10:33,027 --> 00:10:34,818
There you go.

45
00:10:38,671 --> 00:10:42,164
There.
- Thank you.

46
00:10:42,691 --> 00:10:44,958
Not bad for a country preacher.

47
00:10:51,012 --> 00:10:54,234
It's that damn fool Dolarhyde kid.

48
00:10:55,079 --> 00:10:57,391
Hey, hey hey hey!
What are you doing?

49
00:10:57,391 --> 00:10:59,272
Percy, there's people out there.

50
00:10:59,272 --> 00:11:01,026
There's no-one out there, it's fine.

51
00:11:01,026 --> 00:11:03,328
It's not fine. It's bad enough
he drinks for free...

52
00:11:03,328 --> 00:11:05,493
..and now he's gonna shoot up the place?

53
00:11:05,593 --> 00:11:07,131
Hey what was that, doc?

54
00:11:07,131 --> 00:11:10,616
Nothing. He didn's say anything.
Everything's okay. -Go back inside.

55
00:11:10,616 --> 00:11:12,359
Shut up.

56
00:11:13,942 --> 00:11:18,045
I wanna hear what you said.
It's bad enough... what?

57
00:11:19,560 --> 00:11:22,320
Are you ungrateful for our business?

58
00:11:22,426 --> 00:11:24,887
Because if it wasn't
for my Pa's cattle,

59
00:11:24,887 --> 00:11:27,048
There'll be no money going
through this town

60
00:11:27,048 --> 00:11:29,782
And there would be no
meat on your tables

61
00:11:29,782 --> 00:11:33,251
And your doors would
be closed. Huh?

62
00:11:33,756 --> 00:11:36,640
I don't mean no disrespect to your
father, Percy. You know that.

63
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:40,390
Of course not. But you ask me to pay.

64
00:11:42,167 --> 00:11:44,263
Come here, let's settle up.

65
00:11:45,342 --> 00:11:47,089
Come here.

66
00:11:52,188 --> 00:11:57,505
Hey kid, I do not want any trouble.
I'm just trying to...

67
00:11:58,950 --> 00:12:04,004
Better pick up your glasses, doc,
before someone steps on them.

68
00:12:12,283 --> 00:12:16,443
Alright son, we're just trying
to make a living now.

69
00:12:16,610 --> 00:12:20,257
You know what, preacher?
You just gave me an idea.

70
00:12:21,271 --> 00:12:23,702
I know it ain't Sunday, folks, but...

71
00:12:23,838 --> 00:12:27,861
What say we take up a collection
for the poor man, huh?

72
00:12:27,861 --> 00:12:30,728
Now who's got money?

73
00:12:31,817 --> 00:12:34,115
In the hat.

74
00:12:34,521 --> 00:12:37,522
Let's go, much obliged.

75
00:12:37,688 --> 00:12:42,580
I'm sorry, doc's bad fortune has to
be taken out on you good people.

76
00:12:43,602 --> 00:12:45,985
That's mighty Christian of you.

77
00:12:49,972 --> 00:12:51,973
Hey!

78
00:12:53,250 --> 00:12:55,079
You too.

79
00:12:55,217 --> 00:12:59,526
You wanna be careful where you
point that thing before you get hurt.

80
00:13:06,097 --> 00:13:08,560
Listen, eh...

81
00:13:09,030 --> 00:13:14,363
I'm gonna give you the benefit
of the doubt, because...

82
00:13:14,857 --> 00:13:18,224
Maybe you don't know who I am.

83
00:13:31,050 --> 00:13:32,724
Leave me alone.

84
00:13:32,724 --> 00:13:35,175
Hey, you!

85
00:13:36,139 --> 00:13:38,205
I'm warning you.

86
00:13:51,565 --> 00:13:55,072
Where the hell did he come from?

87
00:13:56,015 --> 00:13:58,121
What the hell's going on here?

88
00:13:59,247 --> 00:14:01,372
Well, it was an accident.

89
00:14:01,372 --> 00:14:04,737
He came out of nowhere.
And he dry gulched me.

90
00:14:04,837 --> 00:14:07,159
He tried to make me look like a fool.

91
00:14:07,159 --> 00:14:09,192
It wasn't my fault, Sheriff.

92
00:14:09,192 --> 00:14:11,815
Damn it, Percy. You've crossed
the line this time.

93
00:14:11,915 --> 00:14:12,860
I gotta lock ya up.

94
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:14,732
Taggart.

95
00:14:14,922 --> 00:14:17,735
You know that's not a good idea.

96
00:14:17,846 --> 00:14:20,497
Well I'm afraid I got no choice, Ned.

97
00:14:23,248 --> 00:14:27,763
Ned? Ned, you son of a bitch,
where are you going?

98
00:14:27,910 --> 00:14:33,072
Don't worry. I'll tell your father
about what happened today.

99
00:14:36,570 --> 00:14:38,797
Don't ruin the coffee there, yankee.

100
00:14:38,797 --> 00:14:42,573
Well, tell you what Ed.
The next time you can have coffee.

101
00:14:42,573 --> 00:14:46,302
- Okay, alright. -Hey why don't you take
it easy on that tileslacking, Murphy.

102
00:14:46,302 --> 00:14:48,411
Mr. Dolarhyde don't like
drinking on the job.

103
00:14:48,411 --> 00:14:51,969


104
00:14:53,423 --> 00:14:58,492
I don't give a rat's ass wat the high and
mighty Colonel Dolarhyde don't like.

105
00:14:59,018 --> 00:15:02,247
I don't care how many Indians he put under neither.

106
00:15:02,594 --> 00:15:05,948
You sure do slap your guns a lot
when the boss ain't around.

107
00:15:10,281 --> 00:15:13,253
I'd say it to his face if he was here!

108
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:16,746
Colonel Dolarhyde.

109
00:15:21,919 --> 00:15:25,226
Let me tell you something, boys.

110
00:15:26,824 --> 00:15:29,294
Money makes you soft.

111
00:16:05,873 --> 00:16:08,346
Where the hell is that coach?

112
00:16:08,346 --> 00:16:12,236
- Coach? What coach?
- You shot a deputy, Percy.

113
00:16:12,703 --> 00:16:15,013
Federal Marshal's bringing
you to Santa Fe.

114
00:16:15,022 --> 00:16:19,060
Federal Marshal?
Sherriff, have you lost your mind?

115
00:16:20,058 --> 00:16:22,312
My pa is on his way down here.

116
00:16:22,312 --> 00:16:25,093
you better let me out of here,
before things get out of hand.

117
00:16:25,933 --> 00:16:28,815
Sheriff, it was an accident.

118
00:16:28,815 --> 00:16:31,259
it's not like I'm Jesse James..!

119
00:16:31,259 --> 00:16:33,119
Son of a bitch.

120
00:16:34,165 --> 00:16:37,654
Hey, -your whisky
- can you put that on Percy's tab?

121
00:16:39,372 --> 00:16:41,210
Fifty cents.

122
00:16:41,642 --> 00:16:43,933
Just kidding with you there, pal.

123
00:16:47,177 --> 00:16:49,634
Have they no respect in this town?

124
00:16:49,706 --> 00:16:51,470
That's not true, okay?

125
00:16:52,803 --> 00:16:55,174
- You wanna leave?
- No.

126
00:16:55,174 --> 00:16:57,958
This is your dream.
I'd follow you anywhere.

127
00:16:57,958 --> 00:17:00,191
I thought it was our dream.

128
00:17:01,447 --> 00:17:03,155
God dammit!

129
00:17:03,155 --> 00:17:05,693
Charlie, why don't you play
something festive!

130
00:17:05,693 --> 00:17:08,455
It's like a funeral in here.

131
00:17:13,329 --> 00:17:16,186
Hey. You don't have to
prove anything, okay?

132
00:17:16,570 --> 00:17:18,943
Okay? I love you!

133
00:17:18,943 --> 00:17:20,790
I'm not sure how.

134
00:17:33,909 --> 00:17:35,642
Whisky.

135
00:17:41,422 --> 00:17:43,648
On the house, for what you did.

136
00:18:03,350 --> 00:18:05,499
I'm just here to drink.

137
00:18:10,352 --> 00:18:13,035
Do I know you?
- No.

138
00:18:18,338 --> 00:18:20,440
My name is Ella.

139
00:18:23,273 --> 00:18:25,829
Where did you get your bracelet?

140
00:18:27,684 --> 00:18:30,324
Is there something you
know about me maybe?

141
00:18:32,226 --> 00:18:35,138
You do not remember anything, do you?

142
00:18:38,342 --> 00:18:40,276
What do you want?

143
00:18:40,276 --> 00:18:42,682
I know that you're looking for something.

144
00:18:43,182 --> 00:18:45,205
So am I.

145
00:18:47,169 --> 00:18:49,486
Well, good luck to you.

146
00:18:57,314 --> 00:18:59,475
Move away.

147
00:19:07,371 --> 00:19:09,999
Jake Lonergan.

148
00:19:28,738 --> 00:19:33,462
Follow me to the office, so
we can have us a little chat.

149
00:19:36,446 --> 00:19:39,060
I think you've got the wrong man.

150
00:19:41,197 --> 00:19:44,376
Well, I'm gonna need you to
come with us all the same.

151
00:19:47,661 --> 00:19:50,190
Wouldn't do that if I was you.

152
00:20:20,340 --> 00:20:23,291
I don't want any trouble.

153
00:21:05,586 --> 00:21:08,396
Rise and shine.

154
00:21:11,229 --> 00:21:13,685
You're in trouble now..!

155
00:21:13,765 --> 00:21:15,745
You're gonna burn.

156
00:21:15,745 --> 00:21:18,631
here, my pa is coming for me.

157
00:21:18,814 --> 00:21:23,878
He learned how to kill a man
good, and slow. In the war.

158
00:21:24,164 --> 00:21:27,300
I am gonna watch you suffer...

159
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:33,761
...for a long, long time.

160
00:21:34,802 --> 00:21:39,554
You thought that cheap shot
in the pecker hurt, huh?

161
00:21:47,646 --> 00:21:51,377
Please. I didn't steal your cow.

162
00:21:51,661 --> 00:21:54,741
Colonel Dolarhyde, you've
gotta believe me.

163
00:21:57,051 --> 00:22:00,904
You've only been riding for my
bran for what, two weeks?

164
00:22:02,990 --> 00:22:06,511
You don't maybe know whom
you're dealing with, Roy.

165
00:22:09,821 --> 00:22:12,502
Nobody calls me Colonel.

166
00:22:13,321 --> 00:22:16,133
And them who that did are mostly dead.

167
00:22:19,172 --> 00:22:20,885
Please.

168
00:22:22,612 --> 00:22:26,572
So you had little Mickey's picking
up strays. How many did you get?

169
00:22:26,572 --> 00:22:29,124
About forty-four of 'em, boss.

170
00:22:29,124 --> 00:22:31,427
You've been drinking, ain't
ya? I can smell it on ya.

171
00:22:31,427 --> 00:22:34,728
I haven't been drinking nothing.
You said it yourself, we shouldn't do drinking.

172
00:22:34,828 --> 00:22:39,316
What kind of a man goes 'round
blowing up other peoples cows,

173
00:22:39,316 --> 00:22:42,272
then tells a bullshit story like this?

174
00:22:42,272 --> 00:22:46,291
You could't do no better?
- You gotta believe me, there was a white light.

175
00:22:46,291 --> 00:22:47,884
This bright light.

176
00:22:47,884 --> 00:22:50,285
So there was this big light...

177
00:22:50,285 --> 00:22:53,234
and you fell in the river, and
when you come back...

178
00:22:53,351 --> 00:22:56,682
two of my best hands
has just disappeared.

179
00:22:58,480 --> 00:23:00,271
There weren't no storm...

180
00:23:00,629 --> 00:23:03,758
There weren't no lightning this evening.

181
00:23:03,758 --> 00:23:06,725
You don't respect me, do you Roy?

182
00:23:10,197 --> 00:23:11,847
Where's Percy?

183
00:23:12,010 --> 00:23:14,733
- Taggart locked him up, boss.
- Why?

184
00:23:15,487 --> 00:23:18,712
- What did he do now?
- Shot a deputy.

185
00:23:18,762 --> 00:23:20,597
God dammit.

186
00:23:20,597 --> 00:23:23,426
What the hell does Taggart
think he's doing?

187
00:23:23,426 --> 00:23:25,620
He wouldn't even have a job...

188
00:23:25,774 --> 00:23:28,844
Now I gotta go in there
and reason with him...

189
00:23:28,844 --> 00:23:32,120
...because you failed to
look after my boy.

190
00:23:36,341 --> 00:23:38,778
Thank you. Thank you.

191
00:23:41,316 --> 00:23:43,500
Alright. Everybody saddle up.

192
00:23:48,253 --> 00:23:51,101
Boss, we oughta get more hands.

193
00:23:51,101 --> 00:23:53,672
- Why?
- You're not gonna believe this.

194
00:23:53,772 --> 00:23:56,511
I think Jake Lonergan is in town.

195
00:24:07,839 --> 00:24:10,666
I'm turning you over to the Federal Marshal.

196
00:24:12,488 --> 00:24:14,864
You're gonna tell me
what I'm charged with?

197
00:24:17,080 --> 00:24:20,961
Arson, assault, mayhem...

198
00:24:21,180 --> 00:24:23,302
hijacking...

199
00:24:24,162 --> 00:24:26,390
It says you robbed the stage last month.

200
00:24:26,390 --> 00:24:29,261
With Pat Dolan and Bull McCade.

201
00:24:29,497 --> 00:24:33,260
Which makes you an accesory
to everyone they broke, too.

202
00:24:38,637 --> 00:24:41,822
- Is that it?
- Murder.

203
00:24:43,038 --> 00:24:46,178
Prostitute out in Cottonwood Grove
has con you over.

204
00:24:46,178 --> 00:24:49,242
Name of Alice Wills.

205
00:24:50,384 --> 00:24:52,976
You saying I killed this woman?

206
00:24:52,976 --> 00:24:54,930
You tell me.

207
00:25:38,908 --> 00:25:40,661
Oh damn.

208
00:25:44,514 --> 00:25:46,532
Gimme your wrist.

209
00:25:46,608 --> 00:25:49,518
Taggart, what are you doing?

210
00:25:49,594 --> 00:25:53,912
Sheriff, this is going to far, I....

211
00:25:55,164 --> 00:25:57,223
I was just fooling around.

212
00:25:58,599 --> 00:26:00,828
Look, I didn't mean to hurt anybody.

213
00:26:00,885 --> 00:26:03,791
- Go away.
- Listen I'm sorry.

214
00:26:03,791 --> 00:26:06,233
But I had no choice.
I couldn't let you leave.

215
00:26:06,233 --> 00:26:08,687
Well, I'm leaving now.

216
00:26:09,090 --> 00:26:13,317
- I need you.
- If you have got something to say, say it.

217
00:26:13,920 --> 00:26:17,313
I need to know where you came from.

218
00:26:17,569 --> 00:26:19,789
So do I.

219
00:26:21,120 --> 00:26:22,828
Ma'am...

220
00:26:28,288 --> 00:26:30,963
You gov'ners have a nice trip now.

221
00:26:32,710 --> 00:26:35,667
Taggart. Taggart, let me out of here.

222
00:26:36,487 --> 00:26:38,163
Sheriff.

223
00:26:38,728 --> 00:26:40,462
Sheriff..!

224
00:26:41,098 --> 00:26:43,010
What are you doing?

225
00:26:44,069 --> 00:26:46,178
You get back home. Go to bed.

226
00:26:46,178 --> 00:26:50,005
- Please, do not go.
- I have to, Emmett. It's my job.

227
00:26:51,435 --> 00:26:53,190
I don't like it here.

228
00:26:53,666 --> 00:26:57,152
Now your pa is getting things in order
and when he does, he'll send for you.

229
00:26:57,152 --> 00:26:59,285
It's been a year.

230
00:26:59,553 --> 00:27:01,638
Don't worry, he will.

231
00:27:03,002 --> 00:27:05,532
And your mom is buried here.

232
00:27:05,839 --> 00:27:07,948
And you know I can't leave my little girl.

233
00:27:15,364 --> 00:27:18,261
- Taggart.
- Yeah, I see them.

234
00:27:19,134 --> 00:27:21,091
You go inside.

235
00:27:40,504 --> 00:27:42,749
I want my boy, John.

236
00:27:48,727 --> 00:27:51,118
- I knew you'd come for me, Pa.
- Shut up.

237
00:27:51,118 --> 00:27:53,427
i'll deal with you later.

238
00:27:54,907 --> 00:27:57,520
Yes, that's Lonergan, boss.

239
00:28:01,338 --> 00:28:04,998
That's the son of a bitch who
stole my gold, off the coach.

240
00:28:04,998 --> 00:28:06,493
I want that man.

241
00:28:06,493 --> 00:28:08,929
You're gonna have to take it
up with the judge in Santa Fe.

242
00:28:08,929 --> 00:28:12,879
I ain't going to Santa Fe.
You give him to me now.

243
00:28:13,263 --> 00:28:14,752
Or I'm gonna take him.

244
00:28:14,752 --> 00:28:17,996
- What about me, pa?
- I said shut up, boy.

245
00:28:56,706 --> 00:28:59,099
What the hell is that?

246
00:29:17,912 --> 00:29:20,203
What the hell...?

247
00:30:03,297 --> 00:30:05,664
- It's coming back!
- He's coming around.

248
00:30:05,815 --> 00:30:07,691
This one.

249
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:24,864
- Do not move.
- Wait for me.

250
00:30:36,755 --> 00:30:38,132
- Give me your hand.
- What's going on?

251
00:30:38,132 --> 00:30:40,042
- Give me your hand.
- What the hell for?

252
00:30:40,042 --> 00:30:43,292
I'll get us free.
Give me your hand.

253
00:31:02,273 --> 00:31:05,600
Emmett. Come on son.

254
00:31:07,534 --> 00:31:09,254
Grandpa!

255
00:31:12,466 --> 00:31:14,392
- Gimme your hand.
- No!

256
