- Turn your head.

513
01:05:15,915 --> 01:05:17,457
Are you alright?

514
01:05:22,234 --> 01:05:24,075
Let's get in.

515
01:05:43,643 --> 01:05:47,317
- We were flying.
- Yeah.

516
01:05:48,857 --> 01:05:51,412
- I don't want to do that again.
- No.

517
01:07:03,917 --> 01:07:05,904
Hey.

518
01:07:05,904 --> 01:07:08,415
Hey, you stay with me.

519
01:07:09,092 --> 01:07:11,233
Keep talking.

520
01:07:12,073 --> 01:07:14,644
You remember now, don't you?

521
01:07:15,800 --> 01:07:18,994
- What?
- The woman.

522
01:07:20,675 --> 01:07:22,906
Did you love her?

523
01:07:23,833 --> 01:07:28,022
- You can tell me.
- I can't remember.

524
01:07:28,617 --> 01:07:30,283
I mus have...

525
01:07:30,999 --> 01:07:33,246
All I know is that I owe it to her.

526
01:07:33,962 --> 01:07:36,496
I still have to find her.

527
01:07:38,998 --> 01:07:42,131
Sorry. I'm Sorry.

528
01:07:43,573 --> 01:07:47,107
I got ya. I got you.

529
01:07:51,754 --> 01:07:53,735
It's not far now.

530
01:07:55,645 --> 01:07:57,151
You and me...

531
01:07:58,299 --> 01:08:00,902
...We're gonna be just fine.

532
01:08:07,917 --> 01:08:11,016
Is that.. is that them?

533
01:08:11,552 --> 01:08:13,309
Boss!

534
01:08:22,587 --> 01:08:25,911
- I got it. -Give her to me Ned.
Bring her here.

535
01:08:30,866 --> 01:08:34,849
- Here.
- No... give it to her.

536
01:08:44,450 --> 01:08:46,552
Doc?

537
01:08:57,112 --> 01:08:59,098
How is she?

538
01:09:00,968 --> 01:09:04,044
- She's gone.
- No.

539
01:09:05,725 --> 01:09:09,910
She's not gone. She's ...
NOT GONE!

540
01:09:10,630 --> 01:09:12,925
Jake.

541
01:09:13,564 --> 01:09:15,712
She's gone.

542
01:09:49,472 --> 01:09:51,511
- Doc.
- That's it.

543
01:09:51,811 --> 01:09:53,736
Doc!

544
01:10:28,929 --> 01:10:31,606
This is Black Knife.

545
01:10:32,571 --> 01:10:35,224
There's no reasoning with them.

546
01:10:35,224 --> 01:10:38,503
We're all gonna die anyway.
- This is what's left of the Chiricajas.

547
01:10:38,503 --> 01:10:40,067


548
01:10:41,014 --> 01:10:44,863
He saying the white people, they
brought all this evil to his people.

549
01:10:44,863 --> 01:10:47,576
WE brought evil?
Evil was HERE!

550
01:10:47,576 --> 01:10:48,788
You're the evil one.

551
01:10:48,788 --> 01:10:51,247
He saying we've brought the monsters.

552
01:10:51,247 --> 01:10:55,412
We didn't bring the monsters.
Tell him they took our people too.

553
01:10:55,668 --> 01:10:58,747
- Tell him that they took my wife.
- There is no reasoning with 'em.

554
01:12:07,531 --> 01:12:10,501
Sorry, but I could't tell you.

555
01:12:10,749 --> 01:12:12,983
- Are you one of them?
- No.

556
01:12:13,105 --> 01:12:15,425
I'm from a different place.

557
01:12:15,520 --> 01:12:18,373
I took this form, so I could walk among you.

558
01:12:19,891 --> 01:12:21,583
Well, you should have told me.

559
01:12:21,583 --> 01:12:24,414
I didn't know if I could
heal this body.

560
01:12:24,414 --> 01:12:26,990
If I would wake up.

561
01:12:38,119 --> 01:12:40,632
He wants to know where you're from.

562
01:12:50,320 --> 01:12:55,244
- What did she say? -She came from
a place above the stars.

563
01:12:55,244 --> 01:12:59,209
What do you mean, another world?
What does that mean?

564
01:12:59,209 --> 01:13:01,632
- What?
- He says you shouldn't talk.

565
01:13:01,632 --> 01:13:03,257
What do you mean I shouldn't
talk, I got questions.

566
01:13:04,535 --> 01:13:06,663
- You're a guest of the chief.
- Oh now I'm a guest?

567
01:13:06,663 --> 01:13:08,901
I thought I was a prisoner.

568
01:13:09,291 --> 01:13:11,449
You're both big men, great warriors.

569
01:13:11,449 --> 01:13:14,754
Can we just listen to the woman tell her story?
Or whatever she is?

570
01:13:14,754 --> 01:13:16,265
What are they doing here?

571
01:13:16,305 --> 01:13:18,328
They want gold.

572
01:13:20,273 --> 01:13:23,660
Well that's just ridiculous. What are
they gonna do, buy something?

573
01:13:23,917 --> 01:13:26,628
It is as rare to them, as it is to you.

574
01:13:26,846 --> 01:13:28,752
- What about my grandpa?
- What about my wife,

575
01:13:28,752 --> 01:13:32,374
what about the other people,
are they still alive?

576
01:13:32,374 --> 01:13:34,635
If they are, they won't be for long.

577
01:13:36,546 --> 01:13:38,656
They're studying your weaknesses.

578
01:13:38,938 --> 01:13:40,815
These are just scouts.

579
01:13:40,815 --> 01:13:42,782
If we let them leave,
they'll come back with more

580
01:13:42,782 --> 01:13:45,440
and there will be no survivors.

581
01:13:46,191 --> 01:13:48,350
It's what they did to my people.

582
01:13:48,350 --> 01:13:51,025
I came here to make sure it
would not happen again.

583
01:13:51,025 --> 01:13:53,641
But we have to work together.

584
01:13:59,788 --> 01:14:02,851
He says his people will join her.

585
01:14:02,851 --> 01:14:05,677
What do you mean, join her? What's she
gonna do? Where are you gonna go?

586
01:14:05,677 --> 01:14:08,115
We can find them. He knows where they are.

587
01:14:12,145 --> 01:14:14,129
No I don't.

588
01:14:14,873 --> 01:14:18,083
I can't remember anything.
I can't even remember my own name.

589
01:14:21,546 --> 01:14:24,477
He says they will take care of that.

590
01:16:49,087 --> 01:16:54,361
I brought the gold to the house.

591
01:16:55,357 --> 01:16:58,295
It's where she died.

592
01:16:58,447 --> 01:17:01,137
It's not your fault.

593
01:18:09,866 --> 01:18:12,361
I know where they are.

594
01:18:58,222 --> 01:19:00,628
Jesus, Mary and Josef.

595
01:19:02,361 --> 01:19:05,698
- How did they build something like that?
- They arrived in it.

596
01:19:05,787 --> 01:19:07,749
It's their vessel.

597
01:19:07,749 --> 01:19:11,665
That's only the top, the rest is under
ground. It's how they mine for gold.

598
01:19:11,665 --> 01:19:14,052
So there is gold here.

599
01:19:14,372 --> 01:19:16,322
Can they see out of here?

600
01:19:16,322 --> 01:19:18,061
They don't see well in daylight.

601
01:19:18,061 --> 01:19:21,302
They stay under ground,
in caverns where it's dark.

602
01:19:51,433 --> 01:19:53,152
We never even gonna get close.

603
01:19:53,152 --> 01:19:56,704
These flying machines will pick us
off before we even get near it.

604
01:19:56,704 --> 01:19:59,320
There is another way in.

605
01:19:59,320 --> 01:20:03,014
Down there. The way I came out.

606
01:20:04,903 --> 01:20:07,881
We gotta get those creatures
out of there, out in the open.

607
01:20:07,959 --> 01:20:09,832
where we can get at them.

608
01:20:10,160 --> 01:20:14,073
So you can get in there with that
arm gun, get our people out.

609
01:20:15,203 --> 01:20:18,350
We have one advantage.
They underestimate you.

610
01:20:18,453 --> 01:20:20,394
You are like insects to them.

611
01:20:20,394 --> 01:20:24,016
The're not planning on defending
themselves, so they'll be vulnerable.

612
01:20:24,444 --> 01:20:28,175
- We do not have enough men.
- Obviously they ain't gonna walk.

613
01:20:32,637 --> 01:20:35,857
He says he wants to use
your spyglass.

614
01:21:01,928 --> 01:21:04,552
The Apaches are mountain warriors.

615
01:21:04,735 --> 01:21:08,039
He says it is better to fight from high ground.

616
01:21:10,130 --> 01:21:11,626
Tell him he's a fool.

617
01:21:11,626 --> 01:21:14,760
There's no high ground while
they've got those flying machines.

618
01:21:14,850 --> 01:21:17,028
Jake's leaving.

619
01:21:23,955 --> 01:21:25,497
Well that's just dandy.

620
01:21:25,497 --> 01:21:28,092
Son of a bitch.

621
01:21:30,255 --> 01:21:33,324
- Quit stalling, how much gold we have left?
- Barely enough.

622
01:21:33,324 --> 01:21:37,741
But I'm gonna take my share right now, so I can
get as far away from here as I possibly can.

623
01:21:40,434 --> 01:21:43,650
- Red.
- I have got him, Bull.

624
01:21:49,554 --> 01:21:52,831
Well I had one hell of a job finding you boys.

625
01:21:54,356 --> 01:21:56,363
Are you planning a trip?

626
01:21:59,112 --> 01:22:01,326
We're going as far away as we can go.

627
01:22:01,326 --> 01:22:04,887
- Remember la playa in Porto Vallarta?
- Yeah, you got good fishing.

628
01:22:05,661 --> 01:22:08,405
Good tequila, you wanna come with us?

629
01:22:08,405 --> 01:22:10,467
It will make no difference.

630
01:22:11,747 --> 01:22:13,931
It's not far enough.

631
01:22:15,575 --> 01:22:18,025
Well they ain't worse things, Jake.

632
01:22:18,319 --> 01:22:21,502
Doesn't matter. They're gonna find us.

633
01:22:22,127 --> 01:22:24,340
And they're gonna wipe us out.

634
01:22:24,619 --> 01:22:26,871
What in the hell are you saying?

635
01:22:27,738 --> 01:22:30,312
What I am saying is, you have got a choice.

636
01:22:31,109 --> 01:22:33,878
You can drink your last few
hours away on a beach...

637
01:22:33,878 --> 01:22:37,904
...which, by the way, is not a bad idea...

638
01:22:38,619 --> 01:22:41,602
...or you can follow me one last time.

639
01:22:52,028 --> 01:22:55,127
We've gotta make the best use of our resources.

640
01:22:55,127 --> 01:22:58,216
We've gotta need a strategy.
Listen to me dammit!

641
01:22:59,255 --> 01:23:02,472
He doesn't understand jack.
You've got to explain to him.

642
01:23:02,629 --> 01:23:05,921
Look, we can't just run around hollering

643
01:23:05,921 --> 01:23:09,624
and throwing spears and shooting
arrows at the damn thing.

644
01:23:09,625 --> 01:23:13,655
We gotta draw them outta there,
onto open ground.

645
01:23:13,655 --> 01:23:17,161
Where we can surround them,
attack them on all sides.

646
01:23:17,161 --> 01:23:19,383
Flank 'em.
Explain to him.

647
01:23:23,173 --> 01:23:26,166
He said he's not gonna let you lead his people.

648
01:23:36,447 --> 01:23:38,504
What's he saying?

649
01:23:39,869 --> 01:23:43,854
He saying they need to open their hearts
and see in you what he has seen.

650
01:23:49,735 --> 01:23:52,670
When his parents died in the Mexican war...

651
01:23:53,014 --> 01:23:55,861
...when you took him in when he was only a boy.

652
01:23:58,588 --> 01:24:01,261
That you gave him purpose.

653
01:24:01,342 --> 01:24:04,110
of how to take care of himself.

654
01:24:04,110 --> 01:24:06,473
Even though youre not blood.

655
01:24:10,966 --> 01:24:13,236
That you despise battle.

656
01:24:17,515 --> 01:24:21,244
and you're a fierce warrior, worthy of any fight.

657
01:24:40,368 --> 01:24:44,943
He says if you're such a great warrior, why do you
only have a man and a boy to follow you into battle.

658
01:25:19,947 --> 01:25:21,496
Dog.

659
01:25:21,836 --> 01:25:23,268
Dog!

660
01:25:39,338 --> 01:25:41,381
Hot damn.

661
01:25:42,368 --> 01:25:44,983
Are you ready to get
your son back?

662
01:27:17,484 --> 01:27:19,186
Matches.

663
01:27:30,167 --> 01:27:33,246
I don't know how we're going about this,
we're gonna have to go down...

664
01:27:33,246 --> 01:27:35,242
...I don't know what we're gonna do.

665
01:27:41,988 --> 01:27:44,184
Go.

666
01:27:57,483 --> 01:27:59,256
Go. Go!

667
01:28:38,635 --> 01:28:41,196
I think we've destroyed it.

668
01:28:52,756 --> 01:28:54,780
Demons are coming around us.

669
01:28:58,629 --> 01:29:00,524
Take this and go up where I showed you.

670
01:29:00,524 --> 01:29:02,347
When you see our people, wave your arms.
- Yes, sir.

671
01:29:02,347 --> 01:29:04,256
Move out.

672
01:29:17,752 --> 01:29:19,478
Good job.

673
01:29:19,478 --> 01:29:22,432
Good people you have in there.
I'll get them out.

674
01:29:23,004 --> 01:29:24,653
God speed.

675
01:29:25,437 --> 01:29:27,268
Let's go!

676
01:30:39,570 --> 01:30:42,335
This is how they get the gold out.

677
01:31:06,641 --> 01:31:09,252
They are not going down!
- They will.

678
01:31:09,252 --> 01:31:12,487
Keep at it.
Then we get our people out.

679
01:32:13,579 --> 01:32:15,350
Doc.

680
01:32:15,618 --> 01:32:18,050
Doc, get down here.

681
01:32:20,390 --> 01:32:22,324
Jesus.

682
01:32:24,332 --> 01:32:26,205
Doc!

683
01:32:26,843 --> 01:32:29,245
Did we get one?

684
01:32:29,899 --> 01:32:32,167
Yeah, we got one.

685
01:32:33,593 --> 01:32:38,625
I've always dreamed of
riding into battle with you.

686
01:32:41,279 --> 01:32:44,597
I always dreamed of
having a son like you.

687
01:32:48,173 --> 01:32:51,483
Go. Get Percy.

688
01:32:52,116 --> 01:32:54,813
Get your son.

689
01:34:22,432 --> 01:34:24,961
Don't look into the light.

690
01:34:59,675 --> 01:35:02,463
I told you not to look into the light.
- You're right.

691
01:35:22,059 --> 01:35:25,535
How long are they gonna be like this?
- Each one is different.

692
01:35:30,843 --> 01:35:33,844
Hold them off.
- You better hurry.

693
01:36:14,094 --> 01:36:15,957
There´s more of them coming.

694
01:36:51,118 --> 01:36:52,793
Go.

695
01:37:16,929 --> 01:37:18,676
Everybody is out.

696
01:37:19,107 --> 01:37:20,814
Right.

697
01:37:21,630 --> 01:37:24,146
Hey, where are you going?

698
01:37:24,939 --> 01:37:27,100
It is this way.

699
01:38:16,763 --> 01:38:18,712
Dog, come on.

700
01:39:53,375 --> 01:39:55,745
What the hell are you doing?
We have to get out of here.

701
01:39:55,745 --> 01:39:57,600
No

702
01:39:57,600 --> 01:40:00,647
I came here to destroy that thing.
- How?

703
01:40:01,148 --> 01:40:05,098
- The bracelet. Take it off.
- I can´t take it off.

704
01:40:05,098 --> 01:40:07,483
- Yes you can, you can control it.
- How?

705
01:40:07,483 --> 01:40:10,092
The same way you shoot it, with your mind.

706
01:40:10,997 --> 01:40:13,662
You have to stop thinking.

707
01:40:24,122 --> 01:40:25,952
This isn´t gonna work.

708
01:40:41,088 --> 01:40:43,190
It fell off.

709
01:40:52,355 --> 01:40:55,459
If I can get it to it´s core, I can stop them.

710
01:40:58,091 --> 01:40:59,899
Let´s go.

711
01:41:11,141 --> 01:41:13,149
Take this.

712
01:41:38,512 --> 01:41:40,248
Throw it!

713
01:41:45,073 --> 01:41:47,693
Goodbye, Jake.
- What?

714
01:41:48,162 --> 01:41:50,495
What? No!

715
01:42:53,395 --> 01:42:57,732
I see them. They got out.
They´re coming out through the side.

716
01:42:57,732 --> 01:42:59,928
Do you see Percy?

717
01:43:03,232 --> 01:43:06,064
- Yeah, I see him.
- What about Jake and Ella?

718
01:43:06,286 --> 01:43:08,715
No, they´re not there.

719
01:46:07,319 --> 01:46:09,598
Are you alright old man?

720
01:46:18,417 --> 01:46:20,977
- Where's the girl?
- She´s still inside.

721
01:48:52,533 --> 01:48:54,475
Grandpa.

722
01:48:54,901 --> 01:48:56,962
It's me.

723
01:48:58,474 --> 01:49:01,076
Emmett.
- Emmett.

724
01:49:06,826 --> 01:49:09,270
You´re all grown up.

725
01:49:16,301 --> 01:49:18,306
Percy.

726
01:49:22,791 --> 01:49:25,605
Don´t you remember me, boy?

727
01:49:25,913 --> 01:49:30,496
I´m sorry, I don´t remember much.

728
01:49:31,036 --> 01:49:33,434
I'm your father.

729
01:49:33,708 --> 01:49:35,917
Oh Pa.

730
01:49:45,881 --> 01:49:48,475
Do you remember me?

731
01:50:01,409 --> 01:50:04,681
I thought you were dead.

732
01:51:47,111 --> 01:51:49,773
If there was gold, we could
have made things different.

733
01:51:50,729 --> 01:51:53,515
We´re gonna have a railroad in here soon.

734
01:51:54,300 --> 01:51:56,976
That´ll change the cattle business.

735
01:51:59,405 --> 01:52:02,594
Run these ledgers back to the bank for me, will you?

736
01:52:02,594 --> 01:52:05,543
The foreman needs some new checks.

737
01:52:05,986 --> 01:52:07,671
Okay.

738
01:52:09,143 --> 01:52:13,046
I want the new ones to read "Dolarhyde and Son".

739
01:52:16,133 --> 01:52:18,475
Sound good to you?
- Yes.

740
01:52:19,430 --> 01:52:21,612
Eh, yes, sir.

741
01:52:32,261 --> 01:52:35,385
John.
- Woodrow.

742
01:52:36,610 --> 01:52:39,687
Guess our town is about to get a whole lot bigger.

743
01:52:45,189 --> 01:52:48,441
You weren´t gonna leave without
saying goodbye, were you?

744
01:52:51,571 --> 01:52:53,890
I am a wanted man.

745
01:52:54,468 --> 01:52:59,693
I could have sworn I saw Jake Lonergan
die in those caves, didn´t you, Sheriff?

746
01:52:59,693 --> 01:53:03,997
Damn shame. And I was looking
forward to hanging him myself.

747
01:53:05,659 --> 01:53:09,007
- I could use a good man around here.
- Yes you could.

748
01:53:14,595 --> 01:53:16,804
Jake.

749
01:53:17,964 --> 01:53:20,694
She´s in a better place.

750
01:53:23,868 --> 01:53:26,476
I´ll see you around, Colonel.

751
01:53:48,992 --> 01:53:50,920
The End.
